SIMPLE: incorrupt
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incorrupt
<hw>In`cor*rupt"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incorruptus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Corrupt</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not affected with corruption or decay; unimpaired;
not marred or spoiled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not defiled or depraved; pure; sound; untainted;
above the influence of bribes; upright; honest.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your Christian principles . . . which will preserve you
<qex>incorrupt</qex> as individuals.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Hurd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incorrupted</ent>⟦br⟧
